role: dev
task: S04-T3
title: Status grid and data-dense tactical layout
gate: OPEN
stack_source: @incoming/requirements.md
stack: [TypeScript, React, MobX, Material UI]
requires: [UI]

objective: |
  Introduce status-grid and dashboard-style panels: high-contrast labels, aligned
  data cells, and a "mission control" feel that reads like a tactical briefing.

context:
  - Army-generals WOW implies at-a-glance status, grids, and clear grouping of KPIs/blocks.
  - Glass cards (S02/S03) should wrap panels; layout should support dense information.

steps:
  1. Implement or refine a status-grid pattern: label + value pairs, consistent alignment, glass-card containers.
  2. Apply to key dashboard or list views so critical data appears in clear, scannable blocks.
  3. Use high-contrast labels (e.g. muted but readable) and prominent values (primary/accent).
  4. Ensure responsive behavior: grid collapses or stacks cleanly on smaller viewports.

acceptance-criteria:
  - Status grids and tactical panels are present on primary views.
  - Layout feels data-dense and "command-center" without clutter.
  - Glass-card and dark theme invariants respected.
